{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.38",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 38,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 38",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 38 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:1",
      "text": "Then the Lord answered Job out of a whirlwind, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:2",
      "text": "Who is this that wrappeth up sentences in unskilful words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:3",
      "text": "Gird up thy loins like a man: I will ask thee, and answer thou me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:4",
      "text": "Where wast thou when I laid the foundations of the earth? tell me if thou hast understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:5",
      "text": "Who hath laid the measures thereof, if thou knowest or who hath stretched the line upon it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:6",
      "text": "Upon what are its bases grounded? or who laid the corner stone thereof,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:7",
      "text": "When the morning stars praised me together, and all the sons of God made a joyful melody?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:8",
      "text": "Who shut up the sea with doors, when it broke forth as issuing out of the womb:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:9",
      "text": "When I made a cloud the garment thereof, and wrapped it in a mist as in swaddling bands?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:10",
      "text": "I set my bounds around it, and made it bars and doors:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:11",
      "text": "And I said: Hitherto thou shalt come, and shalt go no further, and here thou shalt break thy swelling waves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:12",
      "text": "Didst thou since thy birth command the morning, and shew the dawning of the day its place?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:13",
      "text": "And didst thou hold the extremities of the earth shaking them, and hast thou shaken the ungodly out of it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:14",
      "text": "The seal shall be restored as clay, and shall stand as a garment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:15",
      "text": "From the wicked their light shall be taken away, and the high arm shall be broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:16",
      "text": "Hast thou entered into the depths of the sea, and walked in the lowest parts of the deep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:17",
      "text": "Have the gates of death been opened to thee, and hast thou seen the darksome doors?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:18",
      "text": "Hast thou considered the breadth of the earth? tell me, if thou knowest all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:19",
      "text": "Where is the way where light dwelleth, and where is the place of darkness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:20",
      "text": "That thou mayst bring every thing to its own bounds, and understand the paths of the house thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:21",
      "text": "Didst thou know then that thou shouldst be born? and didst thou know the number of thy days?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:22",
      "text": "Hast thou entered into the storehouses of the snow, or hast thou beheld the treasures of the hail:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:23",
      "text": "Which I have prepared for the time of the enemy, against the day of battle and war?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:24",
      "text": "By what way is the light spread, and heat divided upon the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:25",
      "text": "Who gave a course to violent showers, or a way for noisy thunder:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:26",
      "text": "That it should rain on the earth without man in the wilderness, where no mortal dwelleth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:27",
      "text": "That it should fill the desert and desolate land, and should bring forth green grass?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:28",
      "text": "Who is the father of rain? or who begot the drops of dew?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:29",
      "text": "Out of whose womb came the ice? and the frost from heaven who hath gendered it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:30",
      "text": "The waters are hardened like a stone, and the surface of the deep is congealed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:31",
      "text": "Shalt thou be able to join together the shining stars the Pleiades, or canst thou stop the turning about of Arcturus?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:32",
      "text": "Canst thou bring forth the day star in its time, and make the evening star to rise upon the children of the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:33",
      "text": "Dost thou know the order of heaven, and canst thou set down the reason thereof on the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:34",
      "text": "Canst thou lift up thy voice to the clouds, that an abundance of waters may cover thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:35",
      "text": "Canst thou send lightnings, and will they go, and will they return and say to thee: Here we are?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.36",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:36",
      "text": "Who hath put wisdom in the heart of man? or who gave the cock understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.37",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:37",
      "text": "Who can declare the order of the heavens, or who can make the harmony of heaven to sleep?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.38",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:38",
      "text": "When was the dust poured on the earth, and the clods fastened together?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.39",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:39",
      "text": "Wilt thou take the prey for the lioness, and satisfy the appetite of her whelps,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.40",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:40",
      "text": "When they couch in the dens and lie in wait in holes?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.38.41",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 38,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 38:41",
      "text": "Who provideth food for the raven, when her young ones cry to God, wandering about, because they have no meat?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
